If it were that simple I'd give it my blessing.  What I am *arguing* for is the *best* solution to a problem with the mage class.<br>
<br>
When pet classes had a problem with pathing (for pets), we asked it to be fixed.  They couldn't reasonably fix it, so we got summon companion/silverflank belt.  So-so, but not great.<br>
<br>
When mages had a problem with summoned gear poofing on LD/camping, we asked it to be fixed.  We get a 30 minute time limit.  A pretty good solution.<br>
<br>
If the mage community had simply *settled* for whatever bone VI threw us, we might not have seen solutions even this good, if any.<br>
<br>
If you're content with resigning yourself to the role of being a twitchy rod/item dispenser on raids, more power to you.<br>
